RIYADH: Saudi Arabia announced one death from COVID-19 and 35 new infections on Friday. Of the new cases, 13 were recorded in Riyadh, seven in Jeddah, and three in Makkah. Several other cities recorded one new case each. The total number of recoveries in the Kingdom increased to 538,505 after 42 more patients recovered from the virus. A total of 8,822 people have succumbed to the virus in the Kingdom so far. Over 46.9 million doses of a coronavirus vaccine have been administered in the Kingdom to date.